                                                                                                               Holy bath vigil on Puri beaches
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, March 8: The Puri district administration has placed a stretch of rubber tubes under the sea to safeguard devotees taking a dip in the sea on the occasion of Gobinda Dwadasi today.        
	Some 15 lakh devotees thronged the Puri beaches today for the holy bath. Gobinda Dwadasi  a planetary position said to occur after a gap of 48 years  is marked in the Hindu almanac as an auspicious occasion for Vaishnavites.         
	A dip in the sea on this day is believed to bless devotees and wash them off their sins. The festival was last celebrated in 1961.         
	The tube would demarcate the limit, devotees would know thats its not safe to go further, said district collector Bhaskarjyoti Sharma. Apart from the tube there were lifeguards on boats.         
	The administration had also taken the help of Orissa State Disaster Management Authority volunteers, NCC, police and fire fighters. Sharma said: Arrangements are in place to ensure proper hygiene, transport, communication and supply of drinking water for the pilgrims.                                                                                                                                                                            
